For a family of 5 people, eating 3 cups of beans per person, 15 cups of beans are required.
There are two phases of cooking beans. First, bringing water to a boil. Then, simmering the beans.
Bringing the water to a boil requires 15 kJ/kg of beans. Therefore, 105 kJ of energy are required as cooking energy.
Simmering beans requires about 3 kJ / min. Simmering for 45 minutes requires 200 kJ of energy.
In total, 350 kJ of energy are required.
It is also important to consider the power requirements at each phase.
Bringing the required 5L of water to a boil requires are least 7 kW of power.
A cooking device for beans should also operate well at the low power stage, around 1 kW.
